To Perform a Release Build Using Jenkins:
Ensure Your Code is Pushed to the MAIN Branch:

Make sure that all your changes are committed and pushed to the main branch as discussed earlier.
Verify that the latest changes are present in the main branch in your repository.
Trigger the Release Build in Jenkins:

Go to the Jenkins job page for your project (plainid-management-automation).
Click on the Build with Parameters option (as shown in your image).
Check the PERFORM_RELEASE checkbox to indicate that you want to perform a release build.
Click the Build button to start the build process.
Monitor the Build Process:

After starting the build, monitor the Jenkins job console output to see the progress.
The build will follow the Release Packaging stage, which includes creating a release, performing the necessary steps for packaging, and pushing to the repository.
Verify the Release:

Once the build completes successfully, verify the release by checking the output artifacts and ensuring that the release has been pushed to the correct repository (e.g., Nexus).
Check Python Test Results:

If you have integrated Python tests into the Maven build, you should also check the test results to ensure all tests have passed.

